In recent years, {{ill|siding materials|ja|窯業系サイディング材|qq=draft}} categorized under kilnwork have become increasingly popular in construction. Their short construction time, excellent design properties, and ability to address labor shortages of {{ill|carpenters|ja|大工|qq=draft}} and {{ill|plasterers|ja|左官|qq=draft}} have driven the market demand, capturing approximately 70% of the external wall share in detached housing.

== Education ==

* '''Kilnwork High Schools''': As of April 2021, the {{ill|Aichi Prefectural Seto Kilnwork High School|ja|愛知県立瀬戸窯業高等学校|qq=draft}} was renamed {{ill|Aichi Prefectural Seto Technical High School|ja|愛知県立瀬戸工科高等学校|qq=draft}}, making "kilnwork" as part of school names extinct.
* '''Specialized Kilnwork Schools''': The {{ill|Saga Prefectural Arita Kilnwork College|ja|佐賀県立有田窯業大学校|qq=draft}} remains the sole institution of its kind.

